name: Moorea producens JHB
description: The strain Moorea producens JHB 22AUG96-1 (aka JHB) was collected from Hector Bay, Jamaica, in August of 1996. It was isolated as a mono-algal culture, although remained non-axenic due to the presence of associated heterotrophs (such as Acidobacteria bacterium Mor1, ASM166450v1). Moorea producens JHB was sequenced by Illumina HiSeq platform. In this project, we used a reference genome (Moorea producens PAL 15AUG08-1) to substantially improve the assembly of M. producens JHB.
